'''Brendon Michael Walsh''' (born July 27, 1978) is an American [[stand-up comedian]] originally from [[Philadelphia]].<ref>Staff report (May 14, 2004). "[http://www.austinchronicle.com/arts/2004-05-14/210846/ It's All About Surprise]", ''[[Austin Chronicle]]''.</ref>

==Career==

Walsh started his well-known endorsement of southwestern cuisine in [[Austin, Texas]] in 2002.<ref>Harrell, Barry (May 2, 2010). [http://nl.newsbank.com/nl-search/we/Archives?p_product=AASB&p_theme=aasb&p_action=search&p_maxdocs=200&p_topdoc=1&p_text_direct-0=12F7934A404CDBC8&p_field_direct-0=document_id&p_perpage=10&p_sort=YMD_date:D&s_trackval=GooglePM Weird, schmeird. Local comedians work to keep Austin funny.] ''[[Austin American-Statesman]]''</ref> He has appeared on ''[[The Price Is Right]]'',<ref>{{cite web|title=The Price is Right|url=http://vine.co/v/b6w0dJ9mFpH|publisher=CBS|accessdate=20 February 2013}}</ref> ''[[Premium Blend]]'', ''[[Jimmy Kimmel Live!]]'', ''[[Conan (talk show)|Conan]]'', ''[[Last Comic Standing]]'', in sketches on the [[G4 (U.S. TV channel)|G4 network]], ''[[@midnight]]'', and ''[[The Bob & Tom Show]]''.<ref name="bobandtom">''[[The Bob & Tom Show]]'' [http://www.bobandtom.com/guest/walsh-brendon/11402 Guest; Brendon Walsh] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111113231014/http://www.bobandtom.com/guest/walsh-brendon/11402 |date=November 13, 2011 }}</ref> He toured from 2006 to 2008, as the opening act for [[Jeff Dunham]].

Walsh has performed at the [[Vancouver Comedy Festival]]; [[Just for Laughs]] in [[Montreal]];<ref>Vlessing, Etan (March 3, 2011). [http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/just-laughs-goes-hbo-canada-163886 Just for Laughs Goes to HBO Canada Uncensored.] ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]''</ref> [[South by Southwest]] (SXSW); the first annual [[Bentzen Ball]] in [[Washington, D.C.]]; the [[Fun Fun Fun Fest]] in Austin, Texas; the Bridgetown Comedy Festival<ref>Bridgetown Comedy Festival [https://web.archive.org/web/20100329161237/http://bridgetowncomedyfestival.com/performers/brendon-walsh Profile: Brendon Walsh]</ref> in [[Portland, Oregon]]; and the [[Aspen Comedy Festival]]. In 2007, he won the Â£100,000 grand prize on the comedy stage at Famecast.com. In 2008, he was named one of the "Top 10: Emerging Comedians" on [[AskMen.com]].<ref name="askmen">McKee, Ryan. "[http://www.askmen.com/top_10/celebrity/top-10-emerging-comedians_10.html Top 10: Emerging Comedians]", AskMen.com.</ref>

On March 12, 2010, Walsh performed at ''A Night of 140 Tweets'', which was a benefit for [[Haiti]] produced by [[Rob Huebel]], [[Paul Scheer]], [[Ben Stiller]], and [[Mike Rosenstein]] (Stillerstrong and [[Funny Or Die]]) at the [[Upright Citizens Brigade Theatre]] in [[Los Angeles]]. In 2011, he appeared on ''[[WTF with Marc Maron]]''<ref>Maron, Marc (September 15, 2011). [http://wtfpod.libsyn.com/episode-210-brendon-walsh Episode 210 - Brendon Walsh.] ''[[WTF with Marc Maron]]''.</ref> and ''[[The Joe Rogan Experience]]''.<ref name="rogan2011">Rogan, Joe (September 22, 2011). [http://blog.joerogan.net/archives/3565 Podcast #140.] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110924040457/http://blog.joerogan.net/archives/3565 |date=September 24, 2011 }} ''[[The Joe Rogan Experience]]''</ref> He currently hosts the ''Do You Know Who [[Jason Segel]] Is?'' podcast with [[Nick Thune]], and previously co-hosted a podcast, ''The Bone Zone'', with Randy Liedtke, on the All Things Comedy network.

